    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe have a 'busy' flag https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34493 but currently it must be manually managed.  We also have `Progress` events https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34846 . These two concepts are related but they aren't linked together in any functional sense, yet.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould/can the concepts be linked together somehow? E.g.\n\n- emit the `busy_start` UI event (or whatever UI event is appropriate for e.g. \"busy mouse\")\n- show a global 'busy' icon somewhere (but not in the window-local statuslines, that would be confusing).",
